EcrRepositoryPrefix.Description: The ECRRepositoryPrefix is a custom alias for upstream registry url.

UpstreamRegistryUrl.Description: The upstreamRegistryUrl is the endpoint of upstream registry url of the public repository to be cached

PolicyText.Description: The JSON policy text to apply to your registry. The policy text follows the same format as IAM policy text. For more information, see Registry permissions (https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonECR/latest/userguide/registry-permissions.html) in the Amazon Elastic Container Registry User Guide.

Rules.Description: An array of objects representing the replication rules for a replication configuration. A replication configuration may contain a maximum of 10 rules.

Destinations.Description: An array of objects representing the details of a replication destination.

RepositoryFilters.Description: An array of objects representing the details of a repository filter.

RegistryId.Description: The RegistryId associated with the aws account.

Key.Description: The key name of the tag. You can specify a value that is 1 to 127 Unicode characters in length and cannot be prefixed with aws:. You can use any of the following characters: the set of Unicode letters, digits, whitespace, _, ., /, =, +, and -.

Value.Description: The value for the tag. You can specify a value that is 1 to 255 Unicode characters in length and cannot be prefixed with aws:. You can use any of the following characters: the set of Unicode letters, digits, whitespace, _, ., /, =, +, and -.

ImageTagMutability.Description: The image tag mutability setting for the repository.

RepositoryName.Description: The name to use for the repository. The repository name may be specified on its own (such as nginx-web-app) or it can be prepended with a namespace to group the repository into a category (such as project-a/nginx-web-app). If you don't specify a name, AWS CloudFormation generates a unique physical ID and uses that ID for the repository name. For more information, see https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSCloudFormation/latest/UserGuide/aws-properties-name.html.

RepositoryPolicyText.Description: The JSON repository policy text to apply to the repository. For more information, see https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonECR/latest/userguide/RepositoryPolicyExamples.html in the Amazon Elastic Container Registry User Guide.

Tags.Description: An array of key-value pairs to apply to this resource.
